The paper proposes a method for learning flexible, monotonic functions for low-dimensional machine learning problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also mentions handling categorical or missing data, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of interpolated look-up tables and lattice regression suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also mentions large-scale learning and parallelization, which suggests that it may belong to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category. Finally, the paper includes case studies with real-world problems involving image classification, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
